HEADWORD: Coyotillo
<hw>Co`yo*til"lo</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Mex. Sp.
dim. See <er>Coyote</er>.]</ety> <def>A low rhamnaceous shrub
(<spn>Karwinskia humboldtiana</spn>) of the southwestern United States
and Mexico. Its berries are said to be poisonous to the
coyote.</def>⟦br⟧
